WEBVTT

01:11.375 --> 01:15.041
It's a great place, a beautiful place.
Why you putting up with that?

01:16.083 --> 01:17.250
I don't know.

01:17.333 --> 01:19.875
I'm not sure I wanna go back
to where I was last year.

01:23.416 --> 01:26.416
NETFLIX PRESENTS

02:51.583 --> 02:54.166
You need to empty the trash.
It's overflowing.

02:54.666 --> 02:57.166
I'll take out the trash later.

03:02.708 --> 03:05.375
Are you washing the dishes, Dad?
Leave it. I'll do it later.

03:05.458 --> 03:06.875
You'll do them? What will you do?

03:09.708 --> 03:10.791
Look at how you live.

03:10.875 --> 03:13.208
-This place is-- it-- it's become a--
-A pigsty.

03:13.291 --> 03:16.125
An amusement park attraction
and a pigsty too.

03:16.208 --> 03:20.416
What are all these colors for,
all these little comics, all this stuff?

03:20.500 --> 03:23.125
Every time I come here, I get depressed.

03:23.208 --> 03:25.208
"Your grandmother
kept the apartment spotless."

03:25.291 --> 03:28.083
"You don't work. You don't study."
You haven't said a thing all night.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.083
But congratulations. Now you've said it.

03:30.166 --> 03:33.708
You think you're fucking with me,
but you're only hurting yourself.

03:33.791 --> 03:36.250
You took five exams in two years,
and you call that studying?

03:36.333 --> 03:38.208
Come on, keep going. Make me feel guilty.

03:38.291 --> 03:41.750
Ah, now it's me making you feel guilty?
Now I get it.

03:41.833 --> 03:45.583
Could it be that you're the one making me
say the same things all the time, huh?

03:45.666 --> 03:48.291
I'm trying, Dad.

03:50.333 --> 03:55.125
Why is the shelf still like this?
Are you waiting for me to fix it?

03:55.208 --> 03:58.333
Like the other hideous thing,
that electric palm over there.

04:02.625 --> 04:04.000
What's going on in your head?

04:04.083 --> 04:07.750
What are you thinking?
If there's anything I can do…

04:08.333 --> 04:09.958
Look, I know it's hard.

04:10.041 --> 04:13.583
I know. I understand you.
I used to be just like you.

04:13.666 --> 04:15.750
If it weren't for your grandfather.

04:15.833 --> 04:18.583
Do you really think I cared
about making wine

04:18.666 --> 04:20.666
when the Siena wanted me
for their youth team?

04:21.708 --> 04:24.541
What was I supposed to do,
abandon our family traditions?

04:25.083 --> 04:27.375
And maybe I didn't have much faith
in myself.

04:27.458 --> 04:31.000
Ludovico. Ludovico!

04:31.083 --> 04:33.333
-Yeah.
-Are you even listening to me?

04:33.416 --> 04:34.250
Yes, Dad.

04:34.333 --> 04:36.708
If I bust your balls,
it's because I care about you.

04:36.791 --> 04:37.708
I know.

04:41.250 --> 04:44.000
Okay, I'm going.
Oh, I left your medicine here.

04:47.250 --> 04:49.833
Oh, that's right. What was
that thing you wanted to show me?

04:50.541 --> 04:52.916
Oh, forget it, Dad.
I'll show it to you next time.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.166
Look, I'm gonna give you the money
in a couple of weeks.

04:55.250 --> 04:57.750
-I have to pay the farmworkers first.
-Don't worry about it.

04:57.833 --> 04:59.541
We've started making oil.

04:59.625 --> 05:02.458
We're still experimenting
since it's our first year.

05:02.541 --> 05:06.458
Why don't you come over?
Stay a couple of days.

05:06.541 --> 05:09.458
I'll explain things to you.
We can be together a bit.

05:09.541 --> 05:13.166
-Your mom will be happy.
-Oh, for sure. It's a good idea.

05:14.166 --> 05:15.166
Bye.

05:18.750 --> 05:20.416
-Good evening.
-Hi.

05:45.375 --> 05:46.458
Maybe next time.

06:03.583 --> 06:04.916
Hi, Secco.

06:11.125 --> 06:13.291
Hey, you're looking great.
You look like Platinette.

06:13.375 --> 06:16.500
I was saving my daily "fuck off"
for my wife, but you can have it.

06:16.583 --> 06:18.083
Come on, gimme a drink.

06:31.833 --> 06:33.208
-Is he here?
-Yeah.

06:33.833 --> 06:35.083
Can you tell him?

06:39.708 --> 06:41.166
Mario just got here.

06:43.083 --> 06:46.375
Gimme another, Secco.

07:00.625 --> 07:05.000
All right, then. I'm going for a piss.
My prostate is driving me crazy.

07:05.083 --> 07:08.083
Hey, careful with this, okay?
Don't take your eyes off it for--

07:08.166 --> 07:09.875
Hey!

07:12.291 --> 07:13.166
Shit!

07:15.833 --> 07:17.333
Asshole, stop!

09:18.291 --> 09:20.666
Shh! Quiet, quiet, quiet.

09:20.750 --> 09:24.333
Walk, quiet. Easy, walk.
Let's go to your place.

09:24.416 --> 09:26.958
Where do you live?
Where the fuck do you live?

09:27.041 --> 09:29.666
Where the fuck do you live?
Take me to your place, quick, fast.

09:29.750 --> 09:31.708
Move.

09:31.791 --> 09:33.791
-Do you live alone? Huh?
-Yeah. Yeah.

09:33.875 --> 09:35.458
-Do you live alone?
-Yes.

09:35.541 --> 09:38.083
-Come on, open up. Open up.
-Yeah.

09:41.250 --> 09:43.208
Where the fuck do you live?
Which one is it?

09:43.291 --> 09:45.041
Fuck. It… it's this one.

09:45.125 --> 09:47.375
Open. Come on, open.

09:49.375 --> 09:53.416
Hurry up. Hurry up. Come on, fuck.

09:58.041 --> 09:59.291
-Gimme the keys.
-Yeah, yeah.

09:59.375 --> 10:00.333
Shh, quiet.

10:01.750 --> 10:03.625
And also your phone. Your phone.

10:08.666 --> 10:10.125
-You said you live on your own?
-Huh?

10:10.208 --> 10:11.375
-Do you live on your own?
-Yes.

10:11.458 --> 10:13.416
-Yeah? Get in here.
-Yeah.

10:16.416 --> 10:19.250
All right. Hey. What's wrong?

10:19.333 --> 10:23.000
-Huh? What's wrong? What's wrong?
-Hang on.

10:23.083 --> 10:24.958
Sit down.

10:25.041 --> 10:28.416
Fuck. Hey, talk. Fuck, what is it?

10:28.500 --> 10:30.208
-Panic attack.
-What can I do?

10:30.291 --> 10:32.083
My drops. The bag.

10:32.166 --> 10:34.875
-This one? Yeah?
-Yeah, yeah.

10:34.958 --> 10:36.083
Which one?

10:37.416 --> 10:40.708
How the fuck does it open? How many?

10:41.375 --> 10:43.083
-Ten.
-Let's make it 15.

10:47.708 --> 10:51.708
Fuck.

10:55.041 --> 10:55.875
Ah.

11:03.541 --> 11:04.833
Aw, fuck.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.041
Sit down. Hey, sit down.

11:38.708 --> 11:40.416
Picchio, it's me. Listen up.

11:41.208 --> 11:43.083
I don't give a fuck what time it is.

11:43.166 --> 11:45.500
I need you to send me 20 kids right now.

11:45.583 --> 11:48.625
I need a watchman day and night
outside the condominiums.

11:48.708 --> 11:51.291
They need to work in shifts. I said now!

12:00.916 --> 12:05.208
Ludovico Fazi, is it you?

12:05.291 --> 12:07.125
You can call me Jack.

12:07.916 --> 12:10.166
I'm gonna have to stay here for a while.

12:10.250 --> 12:11.750
They're looking for me.

12:13.958 --> 12:15.041
They know what I look like.

12:15.125 --> 12:18.666
They know I'm in the area,
but I'll find a way to get out, okay?

12:20.083 --> 12:23.291
If you act up,
I'll have to kill you.

12:23.875 --> 12:27.541
However, if you play along, I'll give you
a nice gift for the trouble when I go.

12:27.625 --> 12:28.791
A gift?

12:28.875 --> 12:30.625
Do you hear me when I talk to you?

12:30.708 --> 12:33.333
Listen closely
because I will not repeat myself.

12:33.416 --> 12:36.833
You stay here, nice and quiet.
Forget about the rest of the world.

12:36.916 --> 12:39.750
And when I go, you'll get 5,000 euros.

12:42.041 --> 12:43.166
Cash.

12:43.250 --> 12:44.458
Five thousand?

12:44.541 --> 12:45.750
What did I fucking tell you?

12:49.583 --> 12:50.958
You'll get it when I leave.

12:53.583 --> 12:55.000
You have to earn it though.

12:57.583 --> 13:00.666
So we have a deal.

13:03.083 --> 13:04.000
Hey.

13:05.208 --> 13:06.500
Mind your own fucking business.

13:06.583 --> 13:08.375
-Understood?
-Yeah.

13:17.208 --> 13:19.250
Fucking spies.

13:35.833 --> 13:38.375
I should have been
on the other side of the world by now.

13:45.208 --> 13:46.583
I'm going to sleep now.

13:48.000 --> 13:49.625
It's been a bad night. I'm beat.

13:52.250 --> 13:53.250
Get up!

13:56.375 --> 13:57.458
Now get in there.

13:58.500 --> 14:00.416
Come on.

14:01.541 --> 14:03.041
Didn't we agree on 5,000?

14:03.125 --> 14:05.791
You're gonna spend the night in here.
Where's the key?

14:21.083 --> 14:22.750
He knew about the cameras.

14:23.458 --> 14:25.000
He just didn't care.

14:27.333 --> 14:30.000
And he knew Mario
was carrying a lot of money tonight.

14:32.125 --> 14:34.041
That means he was planning to steal it,

14:34.125 --> 14:37.708
and he was probably hoping
to vanish right after the theft.

14:45.416 --> 14:47.666
"It doesn't matter who you really are."

14:47.750 --> 14:50.875
"What matters is
what other people think you are."

15:08.125 --> 15:12.083
Let's have a little chat
with the genius downstairs.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.125
Bye, Caino.

16:05.833 --> 16:07.750
Right, Mario, let me get this straight.

16:08.833 --> 16:11.333
You put your bag here on the stool.

16:11.416 --> 16:13.375
You got up to go to the bathroom.

16:13.458 --> 16:16.083
The guy pushed you,
grabbed the bag and took off.

16:16.166 --> 16:18.625
Yeah, but I almost caught him.
I swear, Caino.

16:18.708 --> 16:21.541
He fell off his bike
and started running like a madman.

16:21.625 --> 16:23.500
I was right behind him on my bike,
but then--

16:23.583 --> 16:25.125
Then you let him get away.

16:25.208 --> 16:28.083
Mind you,
I wasn't asking for a justification.

16:28.166 --> 16:30.166
I was asking for an explanation.

16:30.916 --> 16:32.541
I'm sorry, Caino.

16:32.625 --> 16:34.125
But I know where he is.

16:34.208 --> 16:36.708
He went into the apartment buildings,
the ones near the market.

16:36.791 --> 16:38.041
His days are numbered. Trust me.

16:38.125 --> 16:40.208
He's hiding in one of the apartments.
That's for sure.

16:40.291 --> 16:41.791
Yeah, you see?

16:44.500 --> 16:46.875
He dropped this.

16:47.541 --> 16:49.625
Here. It's your money.

16:51.000 --> 16:52.083
Hmm.

16:52.916 --> 16:55.375
I got 20 kids down there right now.

16:55.958 --> 16:57.625
They're checking everyone
going in and out.

16:57.708 --> 17:00.458
As soon as this son of a bitch
sticks his nose out, I'm gonna get him.

17:00.541 --> 17:03.041
How are you gonna find him?
Did you see his face?

17:16.625 --> 17:19.291
Do you know what's
the most important thing for a man?

17:21.875 --> 17:23.375
It's their reputation.

17:25.541 --> 17:27.000
It doesn't matter who you really are.

17:27.083 --> 17:29.125
What matters is
what other people think you are.

17:29.208 --> 17:32.458
Your reputation is your destiny,
like your character.

17:32.541 --> 17:35.125
Everyone knows that whoever steals
from me is a dead man.

17:35.666 --> 17:37.875
This is the reputation
I've built for myself,

17:37.958 --> 17:39.875
and I can't have it destroyed
by some random guy.

17:39.958 --> 17:41.375
You understand, yeah?

17:42.000 --> 17:44.000
-Yeah.
-Of course you understand.

17:44.083 --> 17:45.958
You've been working for me for many years.

17:50.958 --> 17:53.333
Do you believe in destiny, Mario?

17:55.500 --> 17:56.708
Yeah, I do.

18:04.125 --> 18:05.250
Then play.

18:05.833 --> 18:07.250
Discover your destiny.

18:37.791 --> 18:40.250
What drives people to gamble?

18:42.875 --> 18:45.541
Is it greed? Poverty?

18:46.291 --> 18:47.583
Loneliness?

18:48.958 --> 18:51.666
Or is it human nature?

18:54.250 --> 18:57.125
The more you lose,
the more you wanna get it back.

18:57.208 --> 18:58.958
And that's all there is to it.

19:00.291 --> 19:02.625
Don't you agree, Mario?

19:26.333 --> 19:27.750
I won!

19:27.833 --> 19:29.000
I won, Caino!

19:29.083 --> 19:31.583
You see? Destiny's on my side!

19:36.541 --> 19:37.666
Yeah.

19:38.333 --> 19:40.958
But you were the one
who believed in destiny, not me.

19:54.416 --> 19:55.458
I'll get him.

19:56.791 --> 19:58.458
Stinking son of a fucking bitch.

19:58.541 --> 20:00.958
Spartaco, watch your language.

20:02.916 --> 20:06.083
I want him here alive. Twenty-four hours.

20:06.166 --> 20:08.000
Or you'd better disappear too.

20:09.666 --> 20:11.958
Take him away and clean up this mess.

20:20.375 --> 20:24.000
Fucking hell! I can't believe he blew
his brains out without batting an eye.

20:24.708 --> 20:26.500
Who? You mean Buzzetti?

20:26.583 --> 20:27.750
Who else?

20:27.833 --> 20:29.625
He's a hit man. He just follows orders.

20:29.708 --> 20:31.375
The real killer is Caino.

20:31.458 --> 20:35.250
Well, for someone who killed
his own brother just for money,

20:35.333 --> 20:37.083
even if no one could prove he did it.

20:37.166 --> 20:40.500
Don't forget the four or five
other deaths he credits himself with.

20:41.833 --> 20:44.708
I hate him. Just hate him.

20:44.791 --> 20:46.458
He thinks he's a fucking god.

20:47.041 --> 20:50.416
When he talks to me,
it's like he's talking to a cockroach.

20:50.500 --> 20:52.291
I understand that, but Mario as well?

20:52.375 --> 20:53.625
Hey, what about Mario?

20:55.208 --> 20:58.000
Don't you say a bad word about Mario.
I've known him since I was 20.

21:00.958 --> 21:02.458
Then what are you saying?

21:02.541 --> 21:06.375
If someone steals my car
and you can't catch the thief,

21:07.250 --> 21:09.333
it's okay for me to kill you?

21:09.416 --> 21:11.500
Caino can't suffer anyone
to be smarter than he is.

21:11.583 --> 21:12.791
Everyone knows that.

21:13.500 --> 21:15.791
He's got an inferiority complex.

21:15.875 --> 21:17.583
Where did you read that, Marzio?

21:18.333 --> 21:20.416
And then who the fuck is he?
Who does he think he is?

21:20.500 --> 21:21.541
Napoleon?

21:22.125 --> 21:25.041
He's a loan shark
who hides behind some betting shop

21:25.125 --> 21:27.208
full of old women and junkies,

21:27.291 --> 21:29.500
bars and restaurants outside of town.

21:29.583 --> 21:31.958
-But he's rolling in it.
-Yeah, so fucking what?

21:32.041 --> 21:35.041
He wears a suit and cologne,
but he's still a fucking beggar.

21:35.125 --> 21:36.291
A guy who fixed fights.

21:37.583 --> 21:39.833
Shitty little megalomaniac.

21:39.916 --> 21:41.916
Mario had three children

21:42.000 --> 21:43.666
and a wife, a total babe by the way.

21:43.750 --> 21:46.500
-Caino had him killed like a dog.
-You know what I heard?

21:46.583 --> 21:50.000
That Caino's been fucking
Mario's wife for a while now.

21:53.125 --> 21:56.708
-What are you talking about? Giulia?
-Yeah. I swear.

21:56.791 --> 21:59.041
And I think
he already wanted him dead for that.

21:59.125 --> 22:01.666
This is just an excuse.

22:01.750 --> 22:03.666
No, no. That's impossible.

22:03.750 --> 22:06.291
You don't touch a friend's woman.
That's just how it is.

22:06.375 --> 22:08.750
And trust me,
Giulia doesn't fuck around either.

22:08.833 --> 22:12.041
I can promise you that.

22:12.125 --> 22:15.500
I hit on her loads of times,
but she never put out.

22:15.583 --> 22:18.375
-She did with Caino though.
-Fill this hole in and shut the fuck up!

22:19.041 --> 22:20.833
-Picchio.
-Oh, it's just Picchio.

22:20.916 --> 22:22.291
Nobody showed up, huh?

22:22.375 --> 22:23.625
Keep your eyes peeled.

22:23.708 --> 22:26.375
Can you take a photo of this guy
with your phone and send it to Picchio?

22:26.458 --> 22:29.041
-Sure. I can do it.
-Good boy.

22:32.625 --> 22:34.375
You can rest easy now, Mario.

22:36.291 --> 22:37.791
Rest in peace, friend.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.583
-That's why they pay so much.
-To hell with 'em.

23:25.666 --> 23:29.208
The administrator is raking it in too,
but he's not risking shit.

23:29.708 --> 23:31.750
He's a bit of a schemer.
You get it?

23:31.833 --> 23:35.083
And if you fall,
they say you should have been careful.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.375
Like Stelvio's cousin. Poor guy.
You remember?

23:39.458 --> 23:42.541
-Ah, of course I do. Yeah.
-May he rest in peace.

24:39.833 --> 24:41.333
Are you wearing one of my shirts?

24:41.416 --> 24:44.291
Yeah, I've also had a shower and a shave.
Do you want a coffee?

24:44.875 --> 24:46.875
-So you used my things?
-Don't be a pain.

24:46.958 --> 24:50.083
My clothes stank of garbage.
When they dry, I'll give yours back.

24:50.166 --> 24:51.916
Do you want a coffee?

24:58.500 --> 25:00.541
Why are you using
my grandmother's antique china cups?

25:00.625 --> 25:01.833
Because these are cups.

25:01.916 --> 25:04.250
You fill them up,
and then you drink from them.

25:06.916 --> 25:08.666
If you want some, come and get it.

25:27.000 --> 25:28.000
Your grandma?

25:29.125 --> 25:31.375
What was she, a singer, a musician?

25:31.458 --> 25:32.791
No, she gave piano lessons.

25:33.750 --> 25:36.375
-Did you put this up?
-Mm-hmm.

25:39.750 --> 25:42.833
-It's broken. It doesn't work.
-"It's broken. It doesn't work."

25:42.916 --> 25:44.333
Is it that difficult to fix?

25:48.458 --> 25:50.875
Here. Wash this one too.

25:58.583 --> 26:00.500
What about these big books?
Were you at school?

26:00.583 --> 26:04.041
What's with the interrogation?
What do you think you are, a cop?

26:07.083 --> 26:08.458
I asked you a question.

26:14.208 --> 26:16.708
-I'm studying economics.
-Haven't taken many exams I bet.

26:17.416 --> 26:21.000
It takes five minutes to figure you out
and write your story from birth to now.

26:22.625 --> 26:23.958
Such a sad story.

26:24.041 --> 26:26.083
Okay, that's enough!

26:26.166 --> 26:28.083
I was just making small talk.

26:28.875 --> 26:32.250
All these movies, comics, unopened
textbooks. What am I supposed to think?

26:32.333 --> 26:34.416
I study the comics. I draw.

26:35.916 --> 26:37.958
-What do you draw?
-I draw my own comics.

26:38.625 --> 26:41.541
-The only thing I've ever been good at.
-I can picture you.

26:42.500 --> 26:44.416
Sitting there
with the light from the lamp, alone.

26:44.500 --> 26:47.041
Always alone. Zero friends.

26:47.125 --> 26:48.875
Do you have a girlfriend at least?

26:51.125 --> 26:53.041
-Of course not.
-Look, I've had two girlfriends.

26:53.125 --> 26:54.916
-A player!
-A thief and a psychologist.

26:55.000 --> 26:57.125
Don't get uppity
or I'll rip your head off.

26:57.708 --> 27:00.375
I don't give a fuck
how you ended up the way you are.

27:01.000 --> 27:03.875
It's probably not your fault,
but it's not mine either.

27:03.958 --> 27:04.958
We clear?

27:12.166 --> 27:13.666
I have a serious illness.

27:13.750 --> 27:15.791
What do you mean? You're sick?

27:24.791 --> 27:25.708
How long?

27:26.666 --> 27:27.583
It's been a year.

27:27.666 --> 27:30.041
Is that what the hat's for?
You're doing chemo?

27:30.666 --> 27:31.750
Chemo?

27:31.833 --> 27:32.750
Yeah.

27:33.333 --> 27:36.125
You do know depression
isn't treated with chemo, right?

27:36.208 --> 27:38.083
-Depression? Fuck off.
-Gimme my hat back!

27:38.166 --> 27:40.333
Take this thing off.
It's not like you're bald.

27:40.416 --> 27:41.833
What do you know about depression?

27:41.916 --> 27:44.416
You stuff yourself with that
bullshit medication in the bathroom

27:44.500 --> 27:47.416
to convince yourself you're sick
and hide like a rat. And you know why?

27:48.000 --> 27:49.416
Because you hate yourself.

27:51.291 --> 27:53.416
You don't need a degree
to understand that.

28:09.250 --> 28:12.208
Listen, the guy who lives across the way,
what does he do, odd jobs?

28:12.291 --> 28:14.708
I saw that he has
cans of paint outside his door.

28:16.458 --> 28:19.708
No, the concierge told me
his wife wanted a new kitchen.

28:19.791 --> 28:22.083
He has a bar. He's a borderline alcoholic.

28:22.166 --> 28:24.250
Would you happen to have
an X-ray in your apartment?

28:24.333 --> 28:25.625
-An X-ray of his wife?
-Yours.

28:25.708 --> 28:28.208
