Listen, since we've
just bumped into each other,

49:05.541 --> 49:07.083
I'd like to ask you something.

49:07.166 --> 49:09.583
I mean, actually,
I've been meaning to ask you for a while,

49:09.666 --> 49:11.750
but I don't know.
I didn't… I didn't wanna be a pain.

49:11.833 --> 49:13.791
You, a pain for me? Of course not.

49:14.416 --> 49:15.500
My thesis.

49:15.583 --> 49:17.750
Italian cinema of the '60s. Dino Risi…

49:18.333 --> 49:20.125
You're an expert, aren't you?

49:20.208 --> 49:21.833
Y-y-yeah, yeah.

49:22.958 --> 49:25.875
Is there any chance
you could help me with it?

49:25.958 --> 49:28.041
-Please… Please don't say no.
-No.

49:28.625 --> 49:30.416
I mean, I mean--

49:30.500 --> 49:32.375
Yes, that is-- it's… it's not a problem.

49:32.458 --> 49:34.583
Absolutely not
and I'm a big fan of Dino Risi.

49:34.666 --> 49:36.208
So, uh, I don't know.

49:36.291 --> 49:39.583
We could watch a few movies,
analyze them together.

49:39.666 --> 49:41.875
-That would be great.
-Um,

49:41.958 --> 49:45.500
<i>A Difficult Life, The Widower,</i>
<i>Scent of a Woman…</i>

49:45.583 --> 49:48.041
Well, what about
if I come to your apartment?

49:48.750 --> 49:49.958
You… You come to my place?

49:51.833 --> 49:54.791
One of my favorite Dino Risi films
is a crime anthology actually,

49:54.875 --> 49:57.666
with Nino Manfredi.
It has such incredible acting.

49:57.750 --> 49:59.875
And it's called<i> I See Naked.</i>

49:59.958 --> 50:03.875
Hey, it took you a long time
to walk up those few steps.

50:04.958 --> 50:07.750
Uh, the, uh,
these are <i>mucho </i>heavy, so…

50:07.833 --> 50:09.333
If you need me, I'll be in the shower.

50:10.125 --> 50:12.250
Yes, yes. Please, come inside.

50:14.875 --> 50:16.541
You want me
to put these on the table here?

50:16.625 --> 50:18.041
Yes, thanks a lot.

50:19.125 --> 50:21.166
-Hey, Ludovico.
-Yeah.

50:21.250 --> 50:23.000
You know
anything about plumbing?

50:23.083 --> 50:24.250
Uh, of course.

50:24.333 --> 50:25.791
It's that damn faucet.

50:25.875 --> 50:28.708
I've asked the manager 300 times
to come sort it out.

50:28.791 --> 50:31.291
Do you think you could maybe--
Ami, can you show him?

50:31.375 --> 50:32.916
Come, come, Ludo.

50:35.041 --> 50:37.125
You see, uh, I turn on the shower.

50:37.208 --> 50:39.541
-And the thing there, it got stuck.
-Mm-hmm.

50:41.416 --> 50:42.333
Um…

50:42.416 --> 50:44.208
That one there.

50:51.708 --> 50:53.833
<i>Sí.</i>

50:53.916 --> 50:56.916
The problem is it's b-burst.

50:57.000 --> 51:00.458
-I'm sorry. I'm… I'm sorry.
-Ludovico.

51:24.083 --> 51:25.166
Piece of shit.

51:28.000 --> 51:29.083
You looking for someone?

51:29.166 --> 51:31.166
-Get out of the way.
-I asked you a question.

51:31.250 --> 51:32.458
Out of the way, asshole.

51:32.541 --> 51:35.250
You're the one who beats up women,
and I'm the asshole, huh?

51:36.625 --> 51:39.375
You go anywhere near Rebecca again,
and you're a dead man.

51:39.458 --> 51:42.125
She's with a friend of mine now.
He's even more dangerous than I am.

51:42.208 --> 51:43.833
She doesn't wanna see you here again.

51:43.916 --> 51:46.583
Show up one more time
and this shitty little face of yours…

51:46.666 --> 51:49.333
…boom! Boom!

51:50.916 --> 51:53.041
-I'll destroy you.
-Mm-hmm.

51:53.125 --> 51:54.416
-Got it?
-Mm-hmm.

51:54.500 --> 51:56.833
-Hmm?
-Mm-hmm.

51:58.500 --> 52:01.000
And you pissed yourself
on top of everything. Some hero you are.

52:01.083 --> 52:03.041
Now get up and get lost. You stink.

52:03.125 --> 52:04.666
-Go on, get.
-I'm… I-I'm going.

52:05.250 --> 52:06.250
Run away.

52:14.083 --> 52:15.000
Hey!

52:15.083 --> 52:17.375
No, no, no, no, easy, easy, bro.
What happened to you?

52:17.458 --> 52:18.916
What the fuck happened to you?

52:19.000 --> 52:21.625
Fucker had a gun. If it weren't for that,
I'd have kicked the shit--

52:21.708 --> 52:24.791
Did he really have a gun, bro?
Listen, does he look like this?

52:27.375 --> 52:29.041
Hey, where you going? Where you--

52:40.875 --> 52:42.916
Thanks anyway.

52:43.000 --> 52:44.541
Jack, you tried your best.

52:44.625 --> 52:47.375
Yeah, come on.
I think it stopped now, no?

52:47.958 --> 52:50.583
Anyway, tomorrow I'll call a plumber,
a good one.

52:52.000 --> 52:53.416
A real one.

52:53.500 --> 52:55.083
I really tried. I'm sorry.

52:55.166 --> 52:56.833
To thank you for your effort,

52:56.916 --> 52:59.166
I'd like to cook my famous paella.

52:59.250 --> 53:02.083
Oh, yeah, sure, come on.
Why don't we have a dinner together?

53:02.166 --> 53:04.000
Tomorrow night? Would you like that?

53:04.083 --> 53:05.000
Do we like that?

53:05.583 --> 53:07.750
Well, yeah, I'd say yes too.

53:07.833 --> 53:10.708
We'll have Italian versus Spanish.
You make paella. We make amatriciana.

53:10.791 --> 53:14.750
If you cook and do
everything else like you do plumbing…

53:21.208 --> 53:22.083
Hmm.

53:22.166 --> 53:24.916
Nothing like this
has ever happened to me before.

53:25.000 --> 53:27.375
I fucking love you, Jack.
Are you my guardian angel?

53:27.458 --> 53:30.750
It's called Stockholm Syndrome.
You fell in love with your kidnapper.

53:30.833 --> 53:32.666
Well, actually,
it's a fucking stroke of luck.

53:32.750 --> 53:34.500
I looked like
such a moron with that shower.

53:34.583 --> 53:37.333
But I told you I couldn't do it.
That's why I asked you to come up.

53:37.416 --> 53:39.916
Anyway, the little Spaniard
was eating you up with her eyes, huh?

53:40.000 --> 53:42.000
We're out of booze,
not to mention, weed.

53:42.083 --> 53:44.041
Well, no,
I should have some here, I think.

53:44.791 --> 53:47.625
I just don't use it often.
It makes me a bit anxious.

53:48.416 --> 53:51.958
But since I'm already anxious,
maybe it'll help me this time.

53:52.041 --> 53:53.625
How long have you smoked weed?

53:53.708 --> 53:55.500
I don't know.
For a while. I don't smoke much.

54:01.583 --> 54:02.583
Alone, obviously.

54:02.666 --> 54:03.708
Always alone.

54:04.666 --> 54:06.250
But maybe next time with Rebecca.

54:13.958 --> 54:15.791
Everything's sorted.
I took care of it.

54:15.875 --> 54:18.083
-You did great. Here.
-And then?

54:18.833 --> 54:21.250
-The rest when we say goodbye.
-Okay.

54:21.333 --> 54:22.875
-Ciao.
-Bye.

54:40.583 --> 54:43.791
Look at this.
You could be my little brother.

54:43.875 --> 54:45.875
'Cause I'm so tall, and you're short.

54:47.166 --> 54:48.583
I wanna be like you.

54:53.166 --> 54:55.166
Do you really think
that I'm better than you?

54:57.583 --> 54:58.583
Look right there.

55:01.416 --> 55:03.041
Stay the way you are.

55:03.125 --> 55:05.458
You don't wanna be like someone else.
Trust me.

55:12.625 --> 55:14.833
I'm a thief.

55:14.916 --> 55:16.166
Always have been.

55:18.208 --> 55:19.750
Started saving a little bit of money

55:19.833 --> 55:22.541
and now I can live off the interest
from this last job.

55:27.416 --> 55:28.916
I have a cover job.

55:29.000 --> 55:32.041
I clean out cellars,
haul stuff away, little jobs like that.

55:32.125 --> 55:34.208
I even provide invoices.

55:36.041 --> 55:37.666
I used to work with my brother.

55:39.916 --> 55:42.333
Everything I know about life,
I learned from him.

55:44.041 --> 55:46.958
Although the more you try to understand
this life, the less you seem to get.

55:47.041 --> 55:48.375
You have a brother?

55:56.875 --> 55:58.916
He's eight years older.

56:00.666 --> 56:03.375
Paolo. We used to steal together.

56:03.458 --> 56:05.708
But he played the saxophone.
He was in a band.

56:06.333 --> 56:08.958
When people say it's the parents' fault
if someone grows up wrong,

56:09.041 --> 56:10.708
I always laugh.

56:11.291 --> 56:14.125
My father died at the farmers market.
It was an accident.

56:16.625 --> 56:19.458
Then my mom a year later.

56:20.500 --> 56:23.750
She was a cleaning lady.

56:25.208 --> 56:28.833
They were good, honest people.
Me and Paolo, thieves.

56:32.083 --> 56:34.500
How come? Don't know.

56:38.458 --> 56:42.458
I was 18
when he left the country.

56:42.541 --> 56:44.500
He would always tell me, "Study."

56:45.791 --> 56:47.333
"And read books."

56:47.416 --> 56:49.916
He would buy them by the dozens.
I still have 'em.

56:51.000 --> 56:55.416
And the helmet. I'd never part with it
because I'm attached to it.

56:56.833 --> 57:01.208
-Yeah, but he still left you by yourself.
-No. No, he even said to me,

57:01.291 --> 57:04.000
"Come with me.
Come on, it'll be a turning point."

57:04.083 --> 57:06.833
But I didn't feel like leaving. Mm.

57:08.416 --> 57:12.708
Then he got together with
this Brazilian girl, nice piece of ass.

57:13.208 --> 57:15.041
I was even a little bit jealous.

57:23.583 --> 57:24.625
Look here.

57:30.541 --> 57:33.458
"Mar do Paraíso." Look at that.

57:33.541 --> 57:35.666
-Damn!
-He sent it to me three years ago.

57:35.750 --> 57:38.958
-Sure you'll find him when you go there?
-I'll find him. I'll find him.

57:39.041 --> 57:41.833
Paolo's a very clever guy.
Everyone must know him.

57:41.916 --> 57:45.708
If this shit didn't fucking happen,
I'd probably already be there right now.

57:47.083 --> 57:48.666
Morning on the beach.

57:49.458 --> 57:52.875
Afternoon in a hammock with a good book.

57:55.000 --> 57:57.208
And at night, clubbing with all the women.

57:59.166 --> 58:01.375
Did you know that
the Nazis would burn books?

58:03.125 --> 58:04.416
They were scared of them.

58:06.500 --> 58:08.500
And they were scared of women too.

58:09.708 --> 58:13.541
You know, the SS encouraged their soldiers
to fuck one another all the time.

58:13.625 --> 58:15.791
So what though?

58:15.875 --> 58:17.875
-I swear it's true.
-But so what?

58:26.083 --> 58:28.958
I used to beg my father
to let me come and live here on my own.

58:31.125 --> 58:33.125
I wanted to show him what I was worth.

58:36.500 --> 58:37.833
I felt like an artist.

58:37.916 --> 58:40.666
I wanted to sort out the apartment
in my own unique way.

58:45.333 --> 58:47.458
But then I locked myself inside it.

58:47.541 --> 58:48.416
Alone.

58:49.125 --> 58:52.125
As you say, always alone.

58:52.208 --> 58:54.958
To be honest, I'd feel lonely
in a place full of people.

58:57.458 --> 58:59.958
I've always felt this way
since I was a kid.

59:01.125 --> 59:04.083
The only world in which I'm happy
is the world of drawings.

59:05.208 --> 59:07.333
I mean, in the world I draw up, you know?

59:07.875 --> 59:09.000
I don't know.

59:09.625 --> 59:12.416
Maybe I'm scared to find out who I am,
scared of discovering myself,

59:12.500 --> 59:15.041
of… of seeing myself.

59:19.041 --> 59:20.875
Of disappointing my folks.

59:20.958 --> 59:22.375
Don't hide behind your parents.

59:22.458 --> 59:24.666
Ludi, you're not a child.
You're too old for that.

59:25.333 --> 59:27.708
You don't have to feel alone.

59:27.791 --> 59:29.541
Humanity is alone.

59:29.625 --> 59:31.208
It's not easy for anyone.

59:34.166 --> 59:36.541
This joint is the fucking shit.

59:36.625 --> 59:40.375
It's making us talk like…
like philosophers.

59:44.166 --> 59:46.208
You know what I think?

59:46.291 --> 59:48.791
-Hmm.
-Don't know.

59:51.333 --> 59:52.958
Well, you make it look pretty easy.

59:53.041 --> 59:55.791
I mean, your answer
to literally everything is "don't know."

59:55.875 --> 59:57.375
I know that I do not know.

59:58.333 --> 59:59.333
Don't know.

1:00:00.208 --> 1:00:03.500
It is ancient wisdom.

1:00:05.833 --> 1:00:07.125
You know who said that?

1:00:08.333 --> 1:00:11.083
Socrates.

1:00:12.041 --> 1:00:13.250
<i>So now that…</i>

1:00:15.666 --> 1:00:19.333
our guy smashed the face of that
stuck-up asshole, we know he has a gun.

1:00:21.708 --> 1:00:23.583
And we know he's in stairwell A.

1:00:27.958 --> 1:00:29.458
We finally found that fucker.

1:00:30.166 --> 1:00:33.208
And how's that? Didn't you
already check that old staircase?

1:00:33.291 --> 1:00:35.416
We checked every apartment, Caino.
We didn't see him.

1:00:37.208 --> 1:00:38.875
You didn't search thoroughly.

1:00:42.208 --> 1:00:44.083
We searched very thoroughly.

1:00:46.500 --> 1:00:49.666
If you had, you would have found him,
but no. Instead, Picchio did.

1:00:50.541 --> 1:00:53.666
And you come here and tell me,
"We finally found that fucker"?

1:00:53.750 --> 1:00:56.791
By the way, your language is
really starting to rub me the wrong way.

1:00:57.416 --> 1:01:00.625
I gave you a second chance,
and yet, you wasted it of course.

1:01:01.500 --> 1:01:02.708
Pearls before swine.

1:01:03.541 --> 1:01:06.916
So people can wrong Caino
and not suffer the consequences.

1:01:07.000 --> 1:01:08.666
That's what everybody will think, right?

1:01:08.750 --> 1:01:10.708
Give him 24 hours, he's gonna find him.

1:01:14.791 --> 1:01:17.208
My debt
to your father ends today, Spartaco.

1:01:20.166 --> 1:01:21.625
You no longer work for me.

1:01:22.625 --> 1:01:25.041
And be grateful
that destiny gave you a good friend

1:01:25.125 --> 1:01:27.041
who can pay
for your mistakes when necessary.

1:01:30.916 --> 1:01:32.750
You believe in destiny, Marzio?

1:01:35.083 --> 1:01:37.500
Marzio! Marzio!

1:01:39.958 --> 1:01:42.375
Look at me. Look at me.

1:01:42.458 --> 1:01:43.541
Marzio.

1:01:44.500 --> 1:01:46.750
Marzio.

1:01:49.541 --> 1:01:50.958
I'll kill you!

1:02:03.000 --> 1:02:05.166
Your father sacrificed his life for me.

1:02:05.666 --> 1:02:07.625
In return, I'm going to spare yours.

1:02:08.291 --> 1:02:09.958
Now get out of here.

1:02:10.541 --> 1:02:13.625
And from this day on,
make sure you never cross my path again.

1:02:41.583 --> 1:02:43.208
It would've been better to kill him.

1:02:43.291 --> 1:02:47.541
There's a time and a place for everything.
Now I want you to go and look for our guy.

1:02:47.625 --> 1:02:49.166
Find out the apartment number.

1:02:50.083 --> 1:02:52.458
And when you find him, take me to him.

1:02:52.541 --> 1:02:54.666
I wanna deal with him myself.
He's earned it.

1:03:29.958 --> 1:03:31.125
Scared, huh?

1:03:31.208 --> 1:03:33.833
-What is wrong with you?
-I was joking. I was joking!

1:03:33.916 --> 1:03:36.708
-What the fuck are you doing?
-I was joking!

1:03:49.625 --> 1:03:53.708
You fucking moron. Get off me.

1:04:40.375 --> 1:04:42.166
You never shoot with your eyes closed.

1:04:43.208 --> 1:04:44.500
If your hand shakes, you miss,

1:04:44.583 --> 1:04:46.875
and if you miss,
you won't have time for the second shot.

1:04:49.083 --> 1:04:50.208
Trintignant.

1:04:55.875 --> 1:04:58.000
Stop, doesn't suit you.

1:04:59.791 --> 1:05:03.041
-How long did I sleep?
-A long time. It's two in the afternoon.

1:05:03.125 --> 1:05:05.625
-You got painkillers? I have a headache.
-Yeah.

1:05:18.333 --> 1:05:19.916
Always here these guys.

1:05:22.416 --> 1:05:24.375
Did you clean up the apartment?

1:05:24.458 --> 1:05:26.666
Yes, sir. I got up early today. All clean.

1:05:30.291 --> 1:05:31.208
Here.

1:05:36.458 --> 1:05:38.000
Another step forward.

1:05:38.541 --> 1:05:39.791
Well done.

1:05:39.875 --> 1:05:41.666
If only your dad could see it now.

1:05:41.750 --> 1:05:45.041
Poor guy. Every time
he leaves me money, I feel really guilty.

1:05:45.125 --> 1:05:46.875
You still have
the 5,000 I promised, right?

1:05:47.583 --> 1:05:49.083
Yes, thank you again.

1:05:56.000 --> 1:05:58.458
How long will it take you
to finish the comic?

1:05:58.541 --> 1:06:01.166
-What do you mean by "how long"?
-You know, how long?

1:06:01.250 --> 1:06:04.458
How long will it take you
to draw it, print it, publish it.

1:06:04.541 --> 1:06:07.750
I don't know.
Could be four to six months tops.

1:06:07.833 --> 1:06:09.000
Okay, let's say a year.

1:06:09.083 --> 1:06:11.958
-Take a sabbatical and I'll finance you.
-A year sabbatical?

1:06:12.041 --> 1:06:15.583
You don't worry about anything.
Just sit there, draw what you like.

1:06:15.666 --> 1:06:18.875
Money's not a problem for me anymore.
There's a fortune in that bag.

1:06:19.708 --> 1:06:21.458
After a year,
if it doesn't work out for you,

1:06:21.541 --> 1:06:23.000
you go back to what you're doing now.

1:06:23.083 --> 1:06:25.333
You're behind with your exams anyway,
aren't you?

1:06:25.416 --> 1:06:26.250
Yeah, I'm behind.

1:06:26.333 --> 1:06:29.083
I already told you.
If you're gonna have to fail in life,

1:06:29.166 --> 1:06:31.250
it's better to fail
at something you like to do.

1:06:31.333 --> 1:06:33.083
Thanks for your faith in me.

1:06:41.041 --> 1:06:42.416
-Hey.
-What?

1:06:42.916 --> 1:06:44.333
What's there to think about?

1:06:45.708 --> 1:06:47.458
I can withdraw the offer.

1:06:51.583 --> 1:06:54.000
Seriously. Who the fuck else
would make you an offer like that?

1:06:55.625 --> 1:06:56.666
You know what?

1:06:58.000 --> 1:06:59.041
I'm gonna try.

1:06:59.125 --> 1:07:02.625
I'll try. I'll try. I'll try.
I'll go for it. I'll focus. I'll do it.

1:07:02.708 --> 1:07:06.125
I'll go ahead and submit the comic,
and if it works out, I'll even publish it.

1:07:06.208 --> 1:07:08.333
I'll even put in a dedication
for you on the front page.

1:07:08.416 --> 1:07:09.750
Dedicate it to Rebecca, Ludovico.

1:07:09.833 --> 1:07:12.875
I just need you to send me
50% of the profits when I'm over there.

1:07:16.166 --> 1:07:17.000
Rebecca.

1:07:18.416 --> 1:07:20.791
No, it's Jack. Shh!

1:07:23.333 --> 1:07:24.208
Huh?

1:07:24.916 --> 1:07:26.583
Paella versus amatriciana?

1:07:29.916 --> 1:07:31.625
That's fine. <i>Hasta la vista.</i>

1:07:31.708 --> 1:07:33.000
May the best win.

1:07:33.083 --> 1:07:34.416
Bye.

1:07:34.500 --> 1:07:36.666
There. In case Rebecca calls you back.

1:07:36.750 --> 1:07:38.250
Just don't call the police on me.

1:07:38.333 --> 1:07:41.708
It's been forever since a girl called me.
Listen, what about the amatriciana?

1:07:41.791 --> 1:07:43.500
Pasta, jowl bacon, pecorino, tomatoes.

1:07:44.541 --> 1:07:45.375
Here.

1:07:48.250 --> 1:07:50.500
Now fuck it. Come on.
Get everything you need.

1:07:51.333 --> 1:07:52.416
Get the fuck out.

1:07:53.500 --> 1:07:54.666
Me, go outside?

1:07:57.250 --> 1:08:00.958
Make sure you act normal when you pass
those kids down there on the scooters.

1:08:01.041 --> 1:08:02.541
-Act normal?
-No.

1:08:02.625 --> 1:08:04.500
Don't act normal. Act Ludovico.

1:08:15.083 --> 1:08:17.458
And then we're gonna add this at the end.

1:08:17.541 --> 1:08:20.416
-Try the sauce, see how it is.
-Ah, you try it.

1:08:20.916 --> 1:08:23.291
Okay, well, it's pretty hot.

1:08:25.125 --> 1:08:26.458
Mm.

1:08:27.625 --> 1:08:29.333
-Wow, it's so good.
-Mm.

1:08:29.416 --> 1:08:31.791
Anyone would screw a guy
who made an amatriciana this good.

1:08:31.875 --> 1:08:35.041
Then say I made it. You know the Spaniard
